@startuml persistent_virtual_network_configuration
!include ../../../../../../tooling/styles/plantuml/structural/deployment-diagram-style.iuml

title Persistent Virtual Network Configuration Architecture\nCentralized switch + VIM replicate config so migrated VMs keep network connectivity

component "VIM\n(Virtual Infrastructure\nManager)" as vim
component "Centralized\nVirtual Switch\n(shared, published)" as cvs

node "Physical Server A" as psa {
  component "Hypervisor A" as hv1
  component "Virtual Server A\n(initial host)" as vsa1
  component "Local switch port\nassignments" as lp1
}

node "Physical Server B" as psb {
  component "Hypervisor B" as hv2
  component "Virtual Server A\n(after move)" as vsa2
  component "Local switch port\nassignments" as lp2
}

vim -down-> cvs : initiates replication\nof switch config
cvs -down-> lp1 : replicate ports +\nnetwork config
cvs -down-> lp2 : replicate ports +\nnetwork config

vsa1 -right-> vsa2 : migrate when\nServer A fails
vsa2 -up-> lp2 : retrieve config\nfrom centralized switch\n(connectivity preserved)

note bottom of psb
  Without this architecture, the destination
  host lacks the required port assignments
  and configuration, so the migrated VM
  loses network connectivity.
end note

note right of vim
  Supporting mechanisms:
  Hypervisor, Logical Network Perimeter
  (consumer isolation pre/post migration),
  Resource Replication
  (replicates switch config and
  network capacity allocations).
end note

@enduml

